Media personality Bonang Matheba during an interview with Azania Mosaka on the ‘Real Talk’ on June 18, 2018 in Johannesburg, South Africa. JOHANNESBURG - South African media personality Bonang Matheba is among the nominees for this year’s African Influencer category at the E! People's Choice Awards. Taking to social media on Monday, Matheba announced the news to her followers and asked for their votes. READ: Bonang Matheba bags global social media award "Your girl’s been nominated for an E! People’s Choice Award, happening in Santa Monica - California! Yay 2019... Thank you @eonlineafrica. 🙏🏽💕🇿🇦💐 To vote, check my stories.... Love overflows!", read the caption. Other African celebrities nominated in the category include Minnie Dlamini Jones, Cassper Nyovest, Wizkid and Tiwa Savage. The People's Choice Awards will take place on 11 November at The Barker Hangar, Santa Monica. Your girl’s been nominated for an E! People’s Choice Award, happening in Santa Monica - California! Yay 2019... Thank you @eonlineafrica. 🙏🏽💕🇿🇦💐 To vote, check my stories.... Love overflows! #BonangMatheba #AfricanInfluencer #PCA A post shared by  Bonang Matheba (@bonang_m) on Sep 9, 2019 at 10:36am PDT